European Stocks Climb for First Time in Three Days as U.S. Futures Advance

-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 
2011-03-08T08:04:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/european-stocks-climb-for-first-time-in-three-days-as-u-s-futures-advance.html
European stocks rose before a report
today that may show German factory orders rebounded in January.
U.S. futures climbed, while Asian shares fluctuated.  Q-Cells SE retreated 1.8 percent after UBS AG downgraded
the solar company.  The benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index climbed 0.5 percent to
282.07 at 8:04 a.m. in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
